    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Mgay Bari is a festival restored by contemporary Truku people upon a common agreement. Mgay Bari is set up to strengthen the cultural integrity of Truku with the influx of Christian faith, the loss of their tradition and the movement petitioning for official recognition, in hopes of reviving the traditional Truku culture.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>感恩祭為當代太魯閣族協商下所復振的族群節日。受到傳統文化流失、基督宗教進入、文化復振與族群正名等因素的影響下，太魯閣人以感恩祭做為族群的共同祭儀，以期振興傳統太魯閣族文化。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
